# Unity Game Demo

A small Unity game prototype created while exploring game development workflows after building an earlier Python game.
The game uses a simple "press space to fly" mechanic. Although the original Unity source project is no longer available, this demo is included to show my early exploration of Unity's scene-based workflow, object behaviour, and visual feedback.

## What I explored

- Unity scene-based development
- Player movement and keyboard input
- Visual feedback and simple game interaction
- Differences between Python-based game development and using a game engine
